<p>The rate of change of a linear function is constant, so you can choose any 2 points to find the slope.</p>
<p>Use \((-2, 3)\) and \((8, -2)\).¬†</p>
<p>\(m=\frac{y_2-y_1}{x_2-x_1}=\frac{-2-3}{8-(-2)}=\frac{-5}{10}=-\frac{1}{2}\)</p>
